# QuantQL — Language Reference v1.0

> A human-readable query language that compiles to a Python backtesting engine.
> Write strategies in plain English-like syntax. No Python knowledge needed.

---

## 1. SCRIPT STRUCTURE

Every QuantQL script follows this order. Only `TICKER`, `BUY WHEN`, and `SELL WHEN` are mandatory — everything else has smart defaults.

```
┌──────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  BACKTEST "Strategy Name"      ← optional    │
│  MARKET   NSE                  ← optional    │
│  TICKER   RELIANCE             ← REQUIRED    │
│  PERIOD   1Y                   ← optional    │
│                                              │
│  USE RSI(14)                   ← optional    │
│  USE MACD(12, 26, 9)          ← optional    │
│                                              │
│  BUY  WHEN <condition>         ← REQUIRED    │
│  SELL WHEN <condition>         ← REQUIRED    │
│                                              │
│  CAPITAL       100000          ← optional    │
│  POSITION_SIZE 100%            ← optional    │
│  STOP_LOSS     5%              ← optional    │
│  TAKE_PROFIT   15%             ← optional    │
│  COMMISSION    0.1%            ← optional    │
│  SLIPPAGE      0.05%           ← optional    │
│                                              │
│  # comments start with #       ← anywhere   │
└──────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

**Rules:**
- One statement per line
- Order doesn't matter (except readability)
- Case-insensitive (`buy when` = `BUY WHEN` = `Buy When`)
- Comments: anything after `#` is ignored
- Strings: wrap in double quotes `"like this"`
- Percentages: number followed by `%` (e.g. `5%`, `0.1%`)

