## 6. SIMULATION RULES

### 6.1 Bar-by-Bar Processing

```
For each bar (after warmup):
  │
  ├─ If position is OPEN:
  │    ├─ Check stop loss        → exit if hit
  │    ├─ Check take profit      → exit if hit
  │    └─ Check SELL condition   → exit if true
  │
  └─ If position is FLAT (no open trade):
       └─ Check BUY condition    → enter if true
```

- Trades execute at the **close price** of the signal bar
- Only **one position** at a time (no pyramiding in v1)
- Long-only in v1 (no short selling yet)

### 6.2 Warmup Period

The first ~60 bars are skipped to let indicators stabilise:

```
60 bars warmup (or 25% of data, whichever is smaller)
├─ RSI needs ~14 bars
├─ MACD needs ~26+ bars
├─ SMA(50) needs 50 bars
└─ Engine waits 60 to be safe
```

Equity is flat during warmup.

### 6.3 End-of-Data Handling

If a position is still open when data ends:
- Forced close at last bar's closing price
- Tagged with `exit_reason = "end_of_data"`
- Included in trade statistics

