## 7. OUTPUT — What You Get Back

### 7.1 Metrics

| Metric              | Description                                      |
|---------------------|--------------------------------------------------|
| Total Trades        | Number of completed round-trip trades            |
| Winners             | Trades with positive P&L                         |
| Losers              | Trades with negative or zero P&L                 |
| Win Rate            | Winners ÷ Total × 100%                          |
| Net P&L             | Total profit/loss after commissions              |
| Total Return        | (Final equity ÷ Starting capital − 1) × 100%    |
| Gross Profit        | Sum of all winning trade P&Ls                    |
| Gross Loss          | Sum of all losing trade P&Ls                     |
| Profit Factor       | Gross Profit ÷ |Gross Loss|                     |
| Avg Win             | Mean P&L of winning trades                       |
| Avg Loss            | Mean P&L of losing trades                        |
| Avg Win/Loss Ratio  | |Avg Win| ÷ |Avg Loss|                          |
| Max Consec Wins     | Longest winning streak                           |
| Max Consec Losses   | Longest losing streak                            |
| Avg Hold (days)     | Average trade duration                           |
| Total Commission    | Total brokerage paid                             |
| Sharpe Ratio        | Risk-adjusted return (annualised)                |
| Max Drawdown        | Largest peak-to-trough equity drop               |
| Volatility (ann)    | Annualised standard deviation of returns         |
| Starting Capital    | What you started with                            |
| Final Equity        | What you ended with                              |

### 7.2 Trade Log

Each trade records:
```
Entry Date    → when BUY triggered
Exit Date     → when SELL/SL/TP triggered
Entry Price   → close price at entry bar
Exit Price    → close price at exit bar
Shares        → number of shares bought
P&L           → net profit/loss (after commission)
P&L %         → percentage return on the trade
Exit Reason   → "signal" | "stop_loss" | "take_profit" | "end_of_data"
Commission    → total commission for this trade
```

